"My colleague is very eagerly awaiting the arrival of his new MacBook Pro. This is a necessary purchase as his existing machine is at least six years old and is currently minus three crucial keys, so he can't be called frivolous. However, my MacBook is almost exactly a year old and there seem to have been some significant developments between the issuing of the two machines, such as the introduction of the new ‘chiclet’ keys, the new single-piece body, and the sleek, redesigned mousepad. So, just one year down the line and the laptop has changed in both look and operation."
